tion in the central region of droplet. Thus, the\nregime of asymmetrical expansion is realized if the laser intensity exceeds the\nspallation threshold. The transverse and longitudinal expansion velocities\nobtained in SPH simulations of different regimes of expansion are agreed well\nwith our experimental data.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 5 Jul 2018 06:28:05 GMT"}],"update_date":"2019-02-28"}
